FBIS4-4909 "dreas066_c_94029" FBIS-EAS-94-066 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 North Korea Officials Attend Opening of Sports Contest Officials Attend Opening of Sports Contest SK0504045694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0438 GMT 5 Apr 94 SK0504045694 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- The Mangyongdae prize sports contest opened at the Kim Il-song stadium in Pyongyang Monday. It is traditional games held every year around the birthday of the great leader President Kim Il-song. The nearly 50 events include field and track, basketball, volleyball, wrestling, shooting and swimming. Present at the opening ceremony were Pak Song-chol, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] and vice-president; Kim Chung-nin, secretary of the WPK Central Committee; and other officials concerned, working people, sportsmen and school youth in Pyongyang. The ceremony was followed by a health Taekwon-do exhibition performance and a football game at the stadium.
